1
00:00:34,999 --> 00:00:35,929
[This drama is fictional
and bears no resemblance to reality]

2
00:00:35,929 --> 00:00:36,930
[Some scenes feature AI technology]

3
00:00:36,930 --> 00:00:38,461
[All child and animal scenes
followed strict safety guidelines]

4
00:00:38,461 --> 00:00:40,547
[Episode 3]

5
00:00:47,173 --> 00:00:49,804
Excuse me.

6
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:10,081
Hello, sir.

7
00:01:10,081 --> 00:01:11,721
So this is where you've been.

8
00:01:11,721 --> 00:01:14,171
You got here faster than I thought.

9
00:01:15,214 --> 00:01:16,999
Wait here. I'll grab you something to wear.

10
00:01:16,999 --> 00:01:19,009
No, I'm okay...

11
00:01:49,885 --> 00:01:51,840
You looked better before you changed.

12
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:53,286
Less douchey.

13
00:01:53,286 --> 00:01:55,629
Go inside and change.

14
00:02:26,436 --> 00:02:28,136
So why'd you come find me?

15
00:02:28,136 --> 00:02:30,956
Aren't you curious how I found you?

16
00:02:30,956 --> 00:02:33,875
Someone's been tailing me
for the past few days.

17
00:02:41,292 --> 00:02:43,312
[Freshness that wins hearts]

18
00:02:59,756 --> 00:03:01,381
<i>What now?</i>

19
00:03:01,381 --> 00:03:03,655
<i>Am I busted?</i>

20
00:03:06,590 --> 00:03:08,416
<i>Hey, Ju Young Jae.</i>

21
00:03:08,416 --> 00:03:10,214
<i>It's been a while.</i>

22
00:03:10,214 --> 00:03:12,016
<i>- He got caught?</i>
- Sorry, Soo Bin.

23
00:03:12,016 --> 00:03:14,124
He asked me to keep it a secret.

24
00:03:17,328 --> 00:03:19,296
You scared me.

25
00:03:19,296 --> 00:03:22,174
I've got a thing about flowers.

26
00:03:23,590 --> 00:03:25,253
That's why I brought it.

27
00:03:25,253 --> 00:03:27,012
Go ahead, hit me.

28
00:03:40,501 --> 00:03:42,103
Thanks to you,

29
00:03:42,103 --> 00:03:46,198
our show hit its highest ratings ever.

30
00:03:46,941 --> 00:03:48,339
So as a thank-you,

31
00:03:48,339 --> 00:03:52,029
I came to ask if you'd come
on the show one more time.

32
00:03:52,029 --> 00:03:54,148
That's a strange way to show thanks.

33
00:03:54,148 --> 00:03:55,241
I'm asking you.

34
00:03:55,241 --> 00:03:56,988
You came all this way just for that?

35
00:03:56,988 --> 00:03:59,423
Well, why'd you turn your phone off?

36
00:03:59,423 --> 00:04:01,298
But hey...

37
00:04:01,298 --> 00:04:03,631
I got to come back home for once.

38
00:04:03,631 --> 00:04:05,168
It's nice.

39
00:04:05,168 --> 00:04:07,128
All thanks to you.

40
00:04:07,128 --> 00:04:08,981
I was hoping for more.

41
00:04:11,281 --> 00:04:12,802
Huh? Your phone works just fine.

42
00:04:12,802 --> 00:04:15,022
Was Jin Su's place called Feast or something?

43
00:04:15,022 --> 00:04:16,304
Where was it again?

44
00:04:16,304 --> 00:04:18,180
Why don't you just look it up
on that working phone?

45
00:04:18,180 --> 00:04:19,790
You're right.

46
00:04:20,474 --> 00:04:22,284
See you, then.

47
00:04:23,185 --> 00:04:24,710
Director!

48
00:04:24,710 --> 00:04:25,725
Director!

49
00:04:25,725 --> 00:04:27,214
Wait!

50
00:04:27,214 --> 00:04:28,445
Director, let me drive you!

51
00:04:28,445 --> 00:04:30,776
Hold on!

52
00:04:30,776 --> 00:04:34,125
If you show up one more time,
my whole life could change.

53
00:04:34,125 --> 00:04:35,784
Take a right at that intersection.

54
00:04:35,784 --> 00:04:37,324
First, my pay goes up.

55
00:04:37,324 --> 00:04:40,505
Then I'd have a steady income,
so I could cut back on out-of-town gigs.

56
00:04:40,505 --> 00:04:43,631
I get so much out of this,
I can't even list it all.

57
00:04:43,631 --> 00:04:45,385
Are you okay with me doing the show?

58
00:04:45,385 --> 00:04:46,645
Of course I am!

59
00:04:46,645 --> 00:04:48,685
My life gets a major upgrade out of this.

60
00:04:48,685 --> 00:04:51,304
Personal feelings? Who cares.

61
00:04:52,557 --> 00:04:54,037
Did Producer Kyung tell you that?

62
00:04:54,037 --> 00:04:56,038
That your life gets better if I do it?

63
00:04:56,038 --> 00:04:58,019
So you'll do it?

64
00:05:01,256 --> 00:05:03,637
<i>Soo Bin, what do I do?</i>

65
00:05:03,637 --> 00:05:06,397
<i>I don't think I can make it today.</i>

66
00:05:06,397 --> 00:05:08,756
Have you eaten?

67
00:05:08,756 --> 00:05:10,638
Do you want to grab a bite?

68
00:05:12,568 --> 00:05:14,153
Enjoy.

69
00:05:14,153 --> 00:05:15,196
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

70
00:05:15,196 --> 00:05:17,022
Thanks for the food.

71
00:05:32,821 --> 00:05:35,256
Why couldn't your mom make it?

72
00:05:35,256 --> 00:05:37,443
- Yeah, I don't know.
- Why not just go to her place?

73
00:05:37,443 --> 00:05:39,379
Why are you meeting her outside?

74
00:05:40,387 --> 00:05:41,945
Yeah...

75
00:05:53,298 --> 00:05:54,527
You mean the day after tomorrow.

76
00:05:54,527 --> 00:05:56,006
- Thanks for the meal.
- Yeah.

77
00:05:56,006 --> 00:05:58,631
- Jin Su's doing well, right?
- Of course.

78
00:05:58,631 --> 00:06:00,449
Same as always.

79
00:06:00,449 --> 00:06:02,095
I'm so sorry, sir.

80
00:06:02,095 --> 00:06:03,424
Please, don't say that.

81
00:06:03,424 --> 00:06:06,004
- Come again.
- I will.

82
00:06:08,298 --> 00:06:11,754
Even if you call me last-minute,
I'll be right there.

83
00:06:11,754 --> 00:06:13,964
You keep calling on me, so of course I will.

84
00:06:13,964 --> 00:06:15,965
Yes, sir. Thank you.

85
00:06:15,965 --> 00:06:18,968
Take care.

86
00:06:18,968 --> 00:06:21,083
They're booking you
for a festival two days out?

87
00:06:21,083 --> 00:06:23,103
It has to be a fill-in gig.

88
00:06:23,103 --> 00:06:26,183
Works for me, though. Fill-ins pay better.

89
00:06:26,183 --> 00:06:28,143
That's how hard I'm hustling.

90
00:06:28,143 --> 00:06:31,279
But if you'd just come on the show?

91
00:06:36,151 --> 00:06:38,237
See? It's peak festival season.

92
00:06:38,237 --> 00:06:40,330
Wait, no. It's Producer Kyung.

93
00:06:41,643 --> 00:06:43,364
- Yes, Producer Kyung.
<i>- Hey, Yi Jae.</i>

94
00:06:43,364 --> 00:06:45,263
<i>Why haven't you reported back?</i>

95
00:06:45,263 --> 00:06:47,128
<i>Is he doing it?</i>

96
00:06:47,729 --> 00:06:49,650
I'm talking to him right now.

97
00:06:49,650 --> 00:06:51,870
He seems pretty busy with his next project.

98
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:53,250
We're working out the schedule.

99
00:06:53,250 --> 00:06:55,909
<i>What if we get axed before that?</i>

100
00:06:55,909 --> 00:06:57,756
<i>Hurry it up already.</i>

101
00:06:57,756 --> 00:07:00,642
I'm working on it.

102
00:07:01,506 --> 00:07:04,229
Why are you so impatient?

103
00:07:05,826 --> 00:07:08,517
- If I go on the show, will things change?
- Hey!

104
00:07:08,517 --> 00:07:11,020
<i>- What?</i>
- If I go on the show,

105
00:07:11,020 --> 00:07:12,250
will Ju Yi Jae's life change?

106
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:15,190
Hey, are you crazy? What's wrong with you?

107
00:07:15,190 --> 00:07:16,264
What?

108
00:07:16,264 --> 00:07:18,924
You said if I went on the show,
your life would get easier.

109
00:07:18,924 --> 00:07:21,204
So that's what I'm doing.

110
00:07:22,715 --> 00:07:25,083
I'll do the show.

111
00:07:47,882 --> 00:07:50,567
Yes, order coming up!

112
00:07:51,726 --> 00:07:53,673
It's two portions,
but I made it more like three.

113
00:07:53,673 --> 00:07:56,281
That one's on the house.

114
00:07:58,381 --> 00:08:00,047
The sashimi's drying out. Where is he?

115
00:08:00,047 --> 00:08:03,298
Sir, we need to hire someone.

116
00:08:03,298 --> 00:08:04,531
Sorry about that.

117
00:08:04,531 --> 00:08:06,659
[SimSim Fisheries]
Here's your sashimi bowl.

118
00:08:06,659 --> 00:08:09,840
- Some side dishes too.
- Sure, I'll bring more.

119
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:10,506
Hey!

120
00:08:10,506 --> 00:08:12,298
It was great.

121
00:08:12,298 --> 00:08:14,339
I'll pay.

122
00:08:14,339 --> 00:08:15,531
Oh, okay.

123
00:08:15,531 --> 00:08:18,011
- Did you enjoy your meal?
- Yes.

124
00:08:18,839 --> 00:08:20,006
Who is this?

125
00:08:20,006 --> 00:08:21,298
[To SimSim Fisheries, stay healthy, Sim Yu Geon]
You know who this is?

126
00:08:21,298 --> 00:08:23,147
- No idea.
- A singer or something?

127
00:08:23,147 --> 00:08:25,339
That's the owner's son.

128
00:08:25,339 --> 00:08:26,387
Handsome, right?

129
00:08:26,387 --> 00:08:29,014
I thought you were his son.

130
00:08:29,014 --> 00:08:34,381
He does look like...

131
00:08:34,381 --> 00:08:35,867
the owner, though.

132
00:08:35,867 --> 00:08:38,267
We went to school together too.

133
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:39,483
You here visiting?

134
00:08:39,483 --> 00:08:42,381
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

135
00:08:42,381 --> 00:08:44,288
Your son is famous?

136
00:08:44,288 --> 00:08:47,423
Yeah, my son's an actor.

137
00:08:47,423 --> 00:08:48,775
- An actor?
- Really?

138
00:08:48,775 --> 00:08:49,815
What's he been in?

139
00:08:49,815 --> 00:08:52,339
He debuted as Friend Three
in "Devil High School,"

140
00:08:52,339 --> 00:08:55,207
stole the show in episode four,
scene 27 of "The Young Master in My Garden,"

141
00:08:55,207 --> 00:08:56,959
and delivered a legendary line

142
00:08:56,959 --> 00:09:00,462
just before the episode eight finale
of "I Won't Love Anymore."

143
00:09:00,462 --> 00:09:03,591
"Director, the car's ready for you."

144
00:09:03,591 --> 00:09:05,975
And many, many more.

145
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:10,491
- You seen it?
- You seen any?

146
00:09:10,491 --> 00:09:12,683
- We've been here too long. Let's go.
- Thanks for the meal.

147
00:09:12,683 --> 00:09:13,832
- Yeah, it was great.
- Thanks for the meal.

148
00:09:13,832 --> 00:09:14,832
- Come again.
- Thanks.

149
00:09:14,832 --> 00:09:17,354
- Come again!
- Yeah.

150
00:09:17,354 --> 00:09:19,412
They haven't seen any of it.
Take all that down.

151
00:09:19,412 --> 00:09:20,802
Yes.

152
00:09:23,736 --> 00:09:25,987
[To SimSim Fisheries, stay healthy,
Sim Yu Geon]

153
00:09:30,464 --> 00:09:33,545
You look gorgeous in this, Ha Na.

154
00:09:42,874 --> 00:09:46,425
I wonder where he's striking poses this time.

155
00:09:46,425 --> 00:09:50,478
[First Love's Smile]
[Casting Audition]

156
00:10:00,173 --> 00:10:02,448
Sim Yu Geon.

157
00:10:03,756 --> 00:10:04,923
Yes.

158
00:10:04,923 --> 00:10:07,203
Yes, come on in.

159
00:10:18,329 --> 00:10:22,920
<i>You're not quite
the right fit for the character.</i>

160
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:24,735
<i>Marriage?</i>

161
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:28,134
<i>I thought I made myself clear.</i>

162
00:10:28,134 --> 00:10:29,259
<i>Then kill him.</i>

163
00:10:29,259 --> 00:10:31,060
[Casting Director]
<i>Yes.</i>

164
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:34,190
<i>Sir...</i>

165
00:10:34,923 --> 00:10:38,173
<i>Can you be certain we're alive?</i>

166
00:10:38,173 --> 00:10:39,729
<i>Next.</i>

167
00:10:39,729 --> 00:10:41,421
<i>That was a bit disappointing.</i>

168
00:11:04,874 --> 00:11:06,463
Ha Na,

169
00:11:06,463 --> 00:11:09,474
your revised schedule's in.

170
00:11:12,047 --> 00:11:14,006
Hold on, Director Kang.

171
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:15,514
Yes?

172
00:11:15,514 --> 00:11:17,561
Why am I the only one off that day?

173
00:11:17,561 --> 00:11:20,944
Is there something else on my schedule
I don't know about?

174
00:11:21,561 --> 00:11:26,775
That day, you have
a joint event with the CEO...

175
00:11:26,775 --> 00:11:28,861
What is it this time?

176
00:11:28,861 --> 00:11:31,161
You need to go accept the major donor award.

177
00:11:31,161 --> 00:11:32,981
Excuse us.

178
00:11:32,981 --> 00:11:34,806
Let's step out.

179
00:11:34,806 --> 00:11:37,347
A picture-perfect mother-daughter moment,

180
00:11:37,347 --> 00:11:39,671
wouldn't that be lovely?

181
00:11:41,582 --> 00:11:45,169
The exemplary mom is the one getting the award.
Why do I have to go?

182
00:11:45,169 --> 00:11:46,879
So I can be your accessory again?

183
00:11:46,879 --> 00:11:49,246
Does that bother you?

184
00:11:49,246 --> 00:11:51,607
Hey, why would that bother you? It's an honor.

185
00:11:51,607 --> 00:11:55,286
I'm bothered because you don't get
why I'm bothered.

186
00:11:55,286 --> 00:11:56,926
You think it ends with me skipping out?

187
00:11:56,926 --> 00:11:59,350
When shooting gets pushed back,
who has to deal with it?

188
00:11:59,350 --> 00:12:01,310
The crew and the other actors, that's who.

189
00:12:01,310 --> 00:12:04,827
That's part of their job.

190
00:12:04,827 --> 00:12:08,317
People with power get to dictate time, too.

191
00:12:08,317 --> 00:12:10,648
Doesn't it embarrass you? Living like that?

192
00:12:10,648 --> 00:12:13,987
I'm so happy you get to live off
your mom's success.

193
00:12:13,987 --> 00:12:16,158
Makes me feel
like all that hard work was worth it.

194
00:12:16,158 --> 00:12:19,407
It's that "living off Mom" talk
that makes me miserable.

195
00:12:19,407 --> 00:12:20,537
Oh, you brat.

196
00:12:20,537 --> 00:12:23,339
You don't even know
what real misery looks like.

197
00:12:25,131 --> 00:12:27,753
If you go around apologizing
on set again like last time,

198
00:12:27,753 --> 00:12:29,923
you think people will respect you for that?

199
00:12:29,923 --> 00:12:31,253
It just makes you look weak.

200
00:12:31,253 --> 00:12:34,009
No, Mom, you're the one making me look weak.

201
00:12:34,009 --> 00:12:36,053
When you mess up, of course you apologize.

202
00:12:36,053 --> 00:12:38,419
And my screw-ups are
usually because of you anyway.

203
00:12:38,419 --> 00:12:39,423
Keep your voice down.

204
00:12:39,423 --> 00:12:42,900
There are rats everywhere out there
trying to dig up dirt.

205
00:12:44,590 --> 00:12:46,493
Oh, CEO An,

206
00:12:46,493 --> 00:12:47,653
I'm so sorry.

207
00:12:47,653 --> 00:12:48,982
I'm a little late, aren't I?

208
00:12:48,982 --> 00:12:51,133
I know you've been waiting a while for me.

209
00:12:51,133 --> 00:12:52,175
So thoughtful.

210
00:12:52,175 --> 00:12:54,982
By the way, who's the girl
doing my Ha Na's hair?

211
00:12:54,982 --> 00:12:56,282
I've never seen her before.

212
00:12:56,282 --> 00:12:57,964
She was originally assigned to Si Hyun,

213
00:12:57,964 --> 00:12:59,756
but she's quick and has a great eye, so...

214
00:12:59,756 --> 00:13:01,421
Swap her out.

215
00:13:01,421 --> 00:13:02,502
Look at that hair.

216
00:13:02,502 --> 00:13:04,373
No taste at all.

217
00:13:04,373 --> 00:13:06,281
Now.

218
00:13:06,281 --> 00:13:08,134
Yes.

219
00:13:12,756 --> 00:13:15,298
Are you serious? Soo Bin is back in town?

220
00:13:15,298 --> 00:13:18,387
Yeah, he just had bibimbap
at our place a little while ago.

221
00:13:18,387 --> 00:13:20,022
And he was with Yi Jae too.

222
00:13:20,022 --> 00:13:22,565
Oh my.

223
00:13:23,431 --> 00:13:27,438
Didn't Director Woo send him off
to the States for school?

224
00:13:27,438 --> 00:13:28,939
He never showed his face around here,

225
00:13:28,939 --> 00:13:31,006
so I figured he was off being a doctor.

226
00:13:31,006 --> 00:13:35,673
So that film director who was on Yi Jae's show
is really Director Woo's son?

227
00:13:35,673 --> 00:13:37,197
That's what I'm saying.

228
00:13:37,197 --> 00:13:40,339
He changed his whole name.
I almost didn't recognize him.

229
00:13:40,339 --> 00:13:42,077
Why did he suddenly become a Lee?

230
00:13:42,077 --> 00:13:43,740
Lee An Woo, was it?

231
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:45,559
Or Lee An Ku?

232
00:13:45,559 --> 00:13:47,039
It's really something.

233
00:13:47,039 --> 00:13:50,840
Yi Jae was the one who was always
running around saying she'd make movies.

234
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:52,367
How did it end up the other way around?

235
00:13:52,367 --> 00:13:53,631
I know, right?

236
00:13:53,631 --> 00:13:55,173
Soo Bin is staying at my place.

237
00:13:55,173 --> 00:13:56,371
- Oh my, you scared me.
- Oh my goodness!

238
00:13:56,371 --> 00:13:57,718
Hey.

239
00:13:57,718 --> 00:13:59,511
What are you doing sitting here?

240
00:13:59,511 --> 00:14:00,721
Waiting for the bus.

241
00:14:00,721 --> 00:14:03,548
Oh, I see.

242
00:14:03,548 --> 00:14:05,292
Oh look. Here they come.

243
00:14:05,292 --> 00:14:05,892
- Oh my.
- Oh my.

244
00:14:05,892 --> 00:14:07,339
- That's them.
- Yi Jae.

245
00:14:07,339 --> 00:14:10,153
It really is them.

246
00:14:11,769 --> 00:14:14,381
See, I told you.

247
00:14:14,381 --> 00:14:17,882
Those two have always been joined at the hip.

248
00:14:17,882 --> 00:14:19,298
How sweet.

249
00:14:19,298 --> 00:14:23,431
But you don't run the guesthouse anymore.

250
00:14:23,431 --> 00:14:26,546
Figured he had his reasons.

251
00:14:27,590 --> 00:14:28,923
The bus is here.

252
00:14:28,923 --> 00:14:29,791
Right.

253
00:14:29,791 --> 00:14:31,937
- Don't get up. Keep doing what you're doing.
- Okay.

254
00:14:31,937 --> 00:14:34,428
- I'm off.
- Bye.

255
00:14:36,673 --> 00:14:38,715
Grandma Jong Sun!

256
00:14:38,715 --> 00:14:41,381
Grandma Jong Sun!

257
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:43,840
She's not here.

258
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:45,548
You give it to her.

259
00:14:45,548 --> 00:14:46,893
Sure.

260
00:14:46,893 --> 00:14:48,960
Hold on a sec.

261
00:15:05,161 --> 00:15:06,864
Here.

262
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:09,046
[Gyeongseong Love Song]
I'm giving this back to you.

263
00:15:12,715 --> 00:15:14,025
You gave me this script

264
00:15:14,025 --> 00:15:16,024
and said you'd wait.

265
00:15:16,024 --> 00:15:18,723
I think it belongs with you now.

266
00:15:21,144 --> 00:15:24,187
So now you're returning my dream?

267
00:15:25,305 --> 00:15:26,804
You sure about that?

268
00:15:26,804 --> 00:15:29,704
What if I rip it up or burn it?

269
00:15:29,704 --> 00:15:33,070
If that's the ending you want, then do it.

270
00:15:33,655 --> 00:15:36,274
I overlooked the fact
that I'm someone from your past

271
00:15:36,274 --> 00:15:38,875
and only thought about moving forward.

272
00:15:38,875 --> 00:15:41,435
I was wrong.

273
00:15:41,435 --> 00:15:45,208
The ending of our story should've
come before the script's ending.

274
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:48,368
I'm sorry. I really mean it.

275
00:15:50,981 --> 00:15:54,568
I'm sorry I didn't see it myself,

276
00:15:54,568 --> 00:15:56,928
and I'm sorry it took so long.

277
00:15:58,555 --> 00:16:01,964
Those years of waiting you talked about,

278
00:16:01,964 --> 00:16:06,021
they were years I didn't want to remember.

279
00:16:09,256 --> 00:16:11,131
<i>All because of that?</i>

280
00:16:11,131 --> 00:16:12,420
<i>You tanked your college
entrance exam over this?</i>

281
00:16:12,420 --> 00:16:14,271
<i>You let a girl ruin your future?</i>

282
00:16:14,271 --> 00:16:15,689
<i>It wasn't because of Yi Jae.</i>

283
00:16:15,689 --> 00:16:17,720
<i>I never wanted to go to medical school.</i>

284
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:18,464
<i>Soo Bin.</i>

285
00:16:18,464 --> 00:16:20,464
<i>- You little!
- Please stop!</i>

286
00:16:20,464 --> 00:16:21,821
<i>Mom!</i>

287
00:16:21,821 --> 00:16:25,039
<i>No!</i>

288
00:16:27,923 --> 00:16:29,079
<i>Hit me.</i>

289
00:16:29,079 --> 00:16:31,128
<i>Until you've gotten it all out.</i>

290
00:16:33,756 --> 00:16:35,964
As punishment,

291
00:16:35,964 --> 00:16:39,462
my father tried to ship me off to the States,

292
00:16:39,462 --> 00:16:42,549
and until I told him myself that I'd obey him,

293
00:16:42,549 --> 00:16:45,393
I wasn't even allowed to leave the house.

294
00:16:51,506 --> 00:16:53,818
It only took ten days.

295
00:16:54,673 --> 00:16:57,488
For me to give up on myself.

296
00:17:00,798 --> 00:17:02,756
<i>I'll go.</i>

297
00:17:02,756 --> 00:17:04,464
<i>To the States.</i>

298
00:17:04,464 --> 00:17:07,540
<i>I'll live the way you want me to.</i>

299
00:17:11,370 --> 00:17:13,017
<i>Good.</i>

300
00:17:14,039 --> 00:17:16,293
<i>That's how it should be.</i>

301
00:17:19,256 --> 00:17:21,038
But,

302
00:17:21,715 --> 00:17:25,105
how could you not give up on me
when I'd given up on myself?

303
00:17:26,840 --> 00:17:29,554
That huge heart of yours

304
00:17:29,554 --> 00:17:32,481
made me even more ashamed of myself.

305
00:17:35,712 --> 00:17:41,274
I'm not asking you
to understand now, or to forgive me.

306
00:17:42,256 --> 00:17:44,006
I just

307
00:17:44,006 --> 00:17:48,456
wanted you to feel a little better.

308
00:17:49,756 --> 00:17:51,576
Right.

309
00:17:51,576 --> 00:17:53,872
That's a relief.

310
00:17:53,872 --> 00:17:56,380
So it wasn't my fault.

311
00:17:57,111 --> 00:18:00,176
There were circumstances you couldn't help.

312
00:18:00,798 --> 00:18:02,695
I see.

313
00:18:10,896 --> 00:18:13,189
But I don't feel better.

314
00:18:14,715 --> 00:18:16,631
You're hitting me with this now

315
00:18:16,631 --> 00:18:18,986
and calling it comfort?

316
00:18:20,131 --> 00:18:22,649
You know the worst way

317
00:18:22,649 --> 00:18:26,296
to be remembered by someone you loved?

318
00:18:26,296 --> 00:18:28,173
Not as the bad guy,

319
00:18:28,173 --> 00:18:30,873
but as a pathetic loser.

320
00:18:31,596 --> 00:18:33,779
You pathetic bastard.

321
00:18:57,739 --> 00:18:58,977
Hey!

322
00:18:58,977 --> 00:19:00,345
Huh?

323
00:19:02,548 --> 00:19:03,608
You're back.

324
00:19:03,608 --> 00:19:05,775
I washed that to put barley tea in,

325
00:19:05,775 --> 00:19:07,506
and you went and stuck flowers in it!

326
00:19:07,506 --> 00:19:09,946
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

327
00:19:09,946 --> 00:19:11,407
- Did you eat?
- Not yet.

328
00:19:11,407 --> 00:19:14,339
What were you doing that you haven't eaten yet?

329
00:19:14,339 --> 00:19:16,494
I was waiting to eat with you.

330
00:19:16,494 --> 00:19:17,647
You sweet talker.

331
00:19:17,647 --> 00:19:18,926
- Let's go inside.
- Okay.

332
00:19:18,926 --> 00:19:20,627
The yard looks clean, doesn't it?

333
00:19:20,627 --> 00:19:22,256
It does look nice.

334
00:19:22,256 --> 00:19:24,093
- Good job.
- Yeah.

335
00:19:27,047 --> 00:19:29,256
You could've called ahead.

336
00:19:29,256 --> 00:19:31,051
I would've made something for you.

337
00:19:31,051 --> 00:19:33,060
Noodles are fine.

338
00:19:35,214 --> 00:19:37,349
I'm still having no luck with the deposit.

339
00:19:37,349 --> 00:19:39,256
Tell the landlord to wait a bit longer.

340
00:19:39,256 --> 00:19:40,435
If worst comes to worst,

341
00:19:40,435 --> 00:19:42,511
I'll just put the shop up for sale.

342
00:19:42,511 --> 00:19:44,731
You said you'd buy the house back.

343
00:19:44,731 --> 00:19:46,431
Now the shop's on the market too?

344
00:19:46,431 --> 00:19:47,971
I'll figure it out.

345
00:19:47,971 --> 00:19:50,526
- Do you think you can?
- I'll just have to find a way.

346
00:19:51,404 --> 00:19:53,006
When will you have it?

347
00:19:53,006 --> 00:19:55,958
I feel terrible making excuses every time.

348
00:19:56,618 --> 00:19:58,961
What about me? Aren't you sorry?

349
00:20:00,229 --> 00:20:03,876
I gave up on feeling sorry for you
because there's just no end to it.

350
00:20:03,876 --> 00:20:07,509
I'm sorry you got stuck with me as a mother.

351
00:20:07,509 --> 00:20:08,630
You better pay me back.

352
00:20:08,630 --> 00:20:10,269
It's not a gift.

353
00:20:10,269 --> 00:20:12,090
You know what this money means to me, right?

354
00:20:12,090 --> 00:20:14,964
I earned this money on boats,
up mountains, and in the mud.

355
00:20:14,964 --> 00:20:17,715
Of course, I know.

356
00:20:17,715 --> 00:20:19,523
But...

357
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:22,943
I saw him on your show.

358
00:20:25,506 --> 00:20:27,531
I'm done.

359
00:20:30,964 --> 00:20:32,070
Mom.

360
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:34,213
Did you know I hit my highest ratings yet?

361
00:20:34,213 --> 00:20:37,192
I'm practically the MVP of our show right now.

362
00:20:37,192 --> 00:20:39,035
Producer Kyung loves me,

363
00:20:39,035 --> 00:20:40,913
and the executive producer
absolutely adores me.

364
00:20:40,913 --> 00:20:42,332
Really?

365
00:20:42,332 --> 00:20:43,915
Well, they should be giving you a raise,

366
00:20:43,915 --> 00:20:46,377
not just showering you with compliments.

367
00:20:46,377 --> 00:20:47,962
Of course they will!

368
00:20:47,962 --> 00:20:49,006
Who do you think I am?

369
00:20:49,006 --> 00:20:51,298
I'm Park Hyun Ok's daughter, Ju Yi Jae!

370
00:20:51,298 --> 00:20:53,692
Girl, you are all talk.

371
00:20:53,692 --> 00:20:55,553
- Leave it, I'll do it.
- No, get out of the way.

372
00:20:55,553 --> 00:20:58,432
- I said I got it.
- Move.

373
00:20:58,432 --> 00:21:02,110
Mom, since when are you so strong?

374
00:21:02,110 --> 00:21:04,896
- I've got it.
- What've you been eating?

375
00:21:04,896 --> 00:21:07,821
What else would I eat? Just rice.

376
00:21:23,298 --> 00:21:26,048
Don't you dare tell Mom about this.

377
00:21:28,298 --> 00:21:30,553
I need extra pay to keep quiet.

378
00:21:33,231 --> 00:21:35,047
You got caught and you're still this shameless?

379
00:21:35,047 --> 00:21:36,850
Pleasure doing business with you.

380
00:21:50,023 --> 00:21:52,776
[2011 Bunam Youth Film Festival Grand Prize
Winner, Ju Yi Jae]

381
00:21:56,404 --> 00:21:58,559
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

382
00:22:04,370 --> 00:22:07,139
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

383
00:22:09,559 --> 00:22:12,423
This cold raw fish soup is on the house.

384
00:22:12,423 --> 00:22:15,882
Look at you. You've gotten even more handsome.

385
00:22:15,882 --> 00:22:18,340
It just makes me so happy
to see you after all this time.

386
00:22:18,340 --> 00:22:19,381
Right?

387
00:22:19,381 --> 00:22:21,798
I'm so happy too.

388
00:22:21,798 --> 00:22:23,515
- Thank you.
- Sure.

389
00:22:23,515 --> 00:22:24,515
Thank you.

390
00:22:24,515 --> 00:22:27,234
Don't mention it. It's not much.

391
00:22:27,234 --> 00:22:29,354
Enjoy your meal. Okay.

392
00:22:29,354 --> 00:22:30,563
Eat up, son.

393
00:22:30,563 --> 00:22:32,099
You too, Mom.

394
00:22:32,099 --> 00:22:35,159
You love wrapping it in white kimchi.

395
00:22:37,029 --> 00:22:38,173
Here, open up.

396
00:22:38,173 --> 00:22:40,456
- Ah.
- Ah.

397
00:22:42,128 --> 00:22:43,408
Is it good?

398
00:22:43,408 --> 00:22:46,287
Everything tastes better when you feed me.

399
00:22:46,287 --> 00:22:48,373
It's been forever since I had raw fish.

400
00:22:48,373 --> 00:22:50,208
That's just because you eat fancy now, right?

401
00:22:50,208 --> 00:22:55,128
Eating with you is the best thing
in the world to me.

402
00:22:55,128 --> 00:22:57,689
I'm sorry I didn't keep in touch more often.

403
00:22:57,689 --> 00:23:00,552
We can just see each other like this now.

404
00:23:00,552 --> 00:23:04,188
I'm just thrilled you're back in Korea.

405
00:23:04,188 --> 00:23:05,964
So today,

406
00:23:05,964 --> 00:23:08,088
it's my treat.

407
00:23:08,088 --> 00:23:09,853
Here, open up.

408
00:23:09,853 --> 00:23:12,237
- Here, careful.
- Ah.

409
00:23:16,298 --> 00:23:18,082
Soo Bin...

410
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:21,497
is it still too hard for you to visit?

411
00:23:22,256 --> 00:23:24,409
Maybe next time.

412
00:23:24,409 --> 00:23:26,543
Your dad's...

413
00:23:27,339 --> 00:23:29,874
not doing this because he hates you.

414
00:23:29,874 --> 00:23:31,674
Mom, please.

415
00:23:35,506 --> 00:23:38,590
Okay. I'm sorry, son.

416
00:23:38,590 --> 00:23:40,853
Stop apologizing...

417
00:23:41,461 --> 00:23:43,275
and get in.

418
00:23:46,464 --> 00:23:48,601
Promise me you'll call
when you come down again.

419
00:23:48,601 --> 00:23:50,268
I'll be waiting.

420
00:23:50,268 --> 00:23:51,724
I will.

421
00:24:02,990 --> 00:24:04,692
Get home safe.

422
00:25:01,798 --> 00:25:05,114
[No Jaywalking]

423
00:25:08,055 --> 00:25:10,820
- I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

424
00:25:26,631 --> 00:25:27,657
<i>I'm not going.</i>

425
00:25:27,657 --> 00:25:29,923
<i>You promised! We'd make movies together!</i>

426
00:25:29,923 --> 00:25:32,044
<i>What does that matter?</i>

427
00:25:50,681 --> 00:25:53,025
What the hell are you doing?

428
00:26:50,366 --> 00:26:52,121
Are you okay?

429
00:26:54,464 --> 00:26:56,957
I just got a little dizzy.

430
00:27:12,715 --> 00:27:14,787
Hey.

431
00:27:14,787 --> 00:27:17,206
I eat carrots now.

432
00:27:18,101 --> 00:27:20,298
I realized I couldn't be a picky eater

433
00:27:20,298 --> 00:27:23,612
if I wanted to survive in this job.

434
00:27:24,673 --> 00:27:29,708
Enough time has passed
for us to change this much.

435
00:27:33,783 --> 00:27:36,084
But why are there...

436
00:27:37,382 --> 00:27:41,048
some things that never get better?

437
00:27:42,770 --> 00:27:46,345
Why do the good memories fade,

438
00:27:47,298 --> 00:27:49,656
but the bad ones...

439
00:27:50,350 --> 00:27:52,739
stay so vivid?

440
00:27:55,381 --> 00:27:58,338
Maybe that's why we have to hold on

441
00:27:58,338 --> 00:28:01,234
to the good ones even tighter.

442
00:28:07,047 --> 00:28:09,271
That's why I'm here.

443
00:28:25,002 --> 00:28:26,128
Yes, Producer.

444
00:28:26,128 --> 00:28:29,096
I just need to head to Jeonju Station, right?

445
00:29:01,244 --> 00:29:02,456
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

446
00:29:11,172 --> 00:29:14,678
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

447
00:29:18,055 --> 00:29:19,881
<i>The title is "Gyeongseong Love Song."</i>

448
00:29:19,881 --> 00:29:22,183
<i>Nan Young is a gisaeng
who dreams of becoming a poet.</i>

449
00:29:22,183 --> 00:29:26,229
<i>But after her best friend is shot and killed,</i>

450
00:29:26,229 --> 00:29:28,481
<i>she lives only for revenge.</i>

451
00:29:28,481 --> 00:29:30,501
[Written and Directed
by Ju Yi Jae & Woo Soo Bin]

452
00:29:37,657 --> 00:29:42,328
<i>Then, a man appears before her
like it's destiny.</i>

453
00:29:42,328 --> 00:29:44,921
<i>None other than the rich young master,
Moo Gyeom!</i>

454
00:29:44,921 --> 00:29:47,750
<i>You have to have the rich heir.</i>

455
00:29:47,750 --> 00:29:50,464
<i>Poetry, booze, and women.</i>

456
00:29:50,464 --> 00:29:54,047
<i>A guy who just enjoys life
without a single care in the world.</i>

457
00:29:54,047 --> 00:29:58,409
<i>How could anyone not fall for a guy like that?</i>

458
00:29:58,409 --> 00:30:00,554
<i>But here's the twist.</i>

459
00:30:00,554 --> 00:30:03,909
<i>He's actually a freedom fighter
hiding behind a playboy mask!</i>

460
00:30:03,909 --> 00:30:05,351
<i>Hold on, it gets better.</i>

461
00:30:05,351 --> 00:30:07,270
<i>The most shocking truth is...</i>

462
00:30:07,270 --> 00:30:11,169
<i>He's the exact enemy
Nan Young has been hunting her whole life.</i>

463
00:30:11,169 --> 00:30:14,840
<i>Revenge or love, that is the question.</i>

464
00:30:14,840 --> 00:30:17,219
<i>- Bang!
- Ugh.</i>

465
00:30:23,871 --> 00:30:27,172
<i>So... does someone end up dying?</i>

466
00:30:28,173 --> 00:30:29,500
<i>Someone has to.</i>

467
00:30:29,500 --> 00:30:31,807
<i>A romance needs to be tragic.</i>

468
00:30:33,882 --> 00:30:36,298
<i>I prefer happy endings, though.</i>

469
00:30:36,298 --> 00:30:41,960
[Gyeongseong Love Song]

470
00:31:10,715 --> 00:31:12,673
- Hey.
- Yeah?

471
00:31:12,673 --> 00:31:16,138
Remember when I came to you
about making movies?

472
00:31:17,381 --> 00:31:19,175
How could I forget?

473
00:31:19,175 --> 00:31:23,588
You showed up with no money, no bags,
just that one script in your hand.

474
00:31:23,588 --> 00:31:25,371
Exactly.

475
00:31:25,371 --> 00:31:27,391
Even when things got tough
and I wanted to quit,

476
00:31:27,391 --> 00:31:29,840
I held onto that script to keep going.

477
00:31:29,840 --> 00:31:32,032
That's why Yi Jae gave it to me.

478
00:31:32,032 --> 00:31:36,719
She was holding onto me so I wouldn't give up,

479
00:31:36,719 --> 00:31:38,785
asking me to keep dreaming together.

480
00:31:39,590 --> 00:31:40,692
I realized it way too late.

481
00:31:40,692 --> 00:31:43,741
And that's exactly
why you worked like crazy to get here.

482
00:31:43,741 --> 00:31:46,370
Is that why I lost her?

483
00:31:46,370 --> 00:31:49,921
I made it this far because of that script,

484
00:31:50,627 --> 00:31:52,792
but maybe having it in my hands is

485
00:31:52,792 --> 00:31:55,927
the exact reason Yi Jae ended up
giving up on everything.

486
00:31:59,006 --> 00:32:01,010
I have no idea what you're talking about.

487
00:32:01,010 --> 00:32:03,143
Just eat your food.

488
00:32:03,834 --> 00:32:08,274
I gave the "Gyeongseong Love Song" script
back to her.

489
00:32:08,274 --> 00:32:11,506
- But she hasn't called me yet.
- What?

490
00:32:11,506 --> 00:32:13,339
Please.

491
00:32:13,339 --> 00:32:15,055
Hold on. What if...

492
00:32:15,055 --> 00:32:16,634
No.

493
00:32:16,634 --> 00:32:18,528
She knows how much that script means to us.

494
00:32:18,528 --> 00:32:19,693
There's no way she'd throw it out.

495
00:32:19,693 --> 00:32:22,446
But the bottom line is,
you don't actually have it on you right now.

496
00:32:22,446 --> 00:32:25,421
- Yeah.
- Okay, that's it. I'm heading back.

497
00:32:25,421 --> 00:32:27,756
I haven't found soft tofu stew
better than LA's anyway,

498
00:32:27,756 --> 00:32:29,745
and I'm sick of you.

499
00:32:29,745 --> 00:32:32,540
I'm officially giving up my dream
of going independent right here.

500
00:32:32,540 --> 00:32:34,820
I'm leaving. I'm out.

501
00:32:34,820 --> 00:32:37,469
You scanned it, right?

502
00:32:38,440 --> 00:32:40,172
Me?

503
00:32:40,172 --> 00:32:41,300
No.

504
00:32:41,300 --> 00:32:44,093
Man.

505
00:32:44,093 --> 00:32:47,270
You're taking this joke way too far.

506
00:32:48,715 --> 00:32:50,670
You're kidding, right?

507
00:32:52,103 --> 00:32:54,526
Just a little closer.

508
00:32:54,526 --> 00:32:55,927
- See you later.
- See you later.

509
00:32:55,927 --> 00:32:57,906
See you later.

510
00:33:05,631 --> 00:33:07,992
Congratulations on your wedding.

511
00:33:07,992 --> 00:33:10,173
Thank you.

512
00:33:10,173 --> 00:33:12,170
These are gorgeous.

513
00:33:13,914 --> 00:33:15,960
Orders just came down from headquarters.

514
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:18,027
We're going with Plan B.

515
00:33:25,943 --> 00:33:27,283
Cut!

516
00:33:27,283 --> 00:33:28,623
Okay.

517
00:33:28,623 --> 00:33:30,554
Alright, we're breaking for lunch.

518
00:33:30,554 --> 00:33:32,339
- Enjoy your lunch.
- Enjoy.

519
00:33:32,339 --> 00:33:35,352
How did that take look?

520
00:33:35,352 --> 00:33:36,437
Thank you.

521
00:33:36,437 --> 00:33:38,703
- Five rolls of gimbap.
- Yeah.

522
00:33:38,703 --> 00:33:40,364
Wait, what? Five rolls?

523
00:33:40,364 --> 00:33:41,704
That Go Sang Yeon...

524
00:33:41,704 --> 00:33:42,924
I grabbed yours for you, though.

525
00:33:42,924 --> 00:33:44,764
And you should eat in the van.

526
00:33:44,764 --> 00:33:46,715
The CEO specifically said
you have to eat inside.

527
00:33:46,715 --> 00:33:48,648
- She told me to tell you...
- I'm eating outside.

528
00:33:48,648 --> 00:33:50,033
But that dress is so uncomfortable.

529
00:33:50,033 --> 00:33:51,664
Just get in and eat with me...

530
00:33:51,664 --> 00:33:53,621
I could do a backflip in this thing.

531
00:33:53,621 --> 00:33:55,404
Don't worry about me and go eat

532
00:33:55,404 --> 00:33:57,543
before Sang Yeon gobbles everything up.

533
00:33:57,543 --> 00:34:00,303
But your dress...

534
00:34:22,828 --> 00:34:24,685
What?

535
00:34:26,947 --> 00:34:28,503
Never mind.

536
00:34:39,298 --> 00:34:42,218
I seriously don't want to film right now.

537
00:34:44,256 --> 00:34:45,718
Sorry?

538
00:34:48,464 --> 00:34:51,339
Is it so wrong to not want to shoot?

539
00:34:51,339 --> 00:34:52,882
No,

540
00:34:52,882 --> 00:34:54,684
that's completely fair.

541
00:34:58,339 --> 00:35:00,940
You didn't get one of these?

542
00:35:00,940 --> 00:35:03,782
Yeah, they said they ran out.

543
00:35:04,756 --> 00:35:06,828
That jerk, Go Sang Yeon.

544
00:35:09,131 --> 00:35:10,798
- Want some?
- I'm good.

545
00:35:10,798 --> 00:35:12,491
I can't finish a whole roll anyway.

546
00:35:12,491 --> 00:35:14,127
Just eat it.

547
00:35:15,163 --> 00:35:17,462
My arm's getting tired.

548
00:35:18,163 --> 00:35:19,766
Well...

549
00:35:20,590 --> 00:35:22,630
Thank you.

550
00:35:43,187 --> 00:35:45,007
You're bored too, right?

551
00:35:45,007 --> 00:35:47,276
Gang Member Number 3.

552
00:35:47,276 --> 00:35:49,067
I actually need to get going.

553
00:35:49,067 --> 00:35:51,167
What?

554
00:35:51,167 --> 00:35:52,747
You're done right after lunch?

555
00:35:52,747 --> 00:35:54,116
Lucky you.

556
00:35:54,116 --> 00:35:57,419
I actually can't leave right now
because of you, Ha Na-nim.

557
00:35:58,456 --> 00:36:01,107
Adding "nim" makes me sound like God.

558
00:36:01,107 --> 00:36:03,347
I'm Buddhist.

559
00:36:03,347 --> 00:36:06,629
Just call me Ha Na.

560
00:36:06,629 --> 00:36:08,154
Right.

561
00:36:09,131 --> 00:36:12,427
That thing you're sitting on is...

562
00:36:12,427 --> 00:36:14,460
my bike.

563
00:36:19,673 --> 00:36:21,296
- Hop on, then.
- What?

564
00:36:21,296 --> 00:36:23,945
Could you just take me for a quick spin?

565
00:36:24,548 --> 00:36:26,357
Come on, I gave you my gimbap.

566
00:36:26,357 --> 00:36:28,525
Just ten minutes.

567
00:36:28,525 --> 00:36:30,339
Or five?

568
00:36:30,339 --> 00:36:33,295
I'll call it even for the food.

569
00:36:33,295 --> 00:36:35,165
Sweet!

570
00:36:39,882 --> 00:36:41,568
Like this?

571
00:37:02,131 --> 00:37:04,590
It's just like "A Moment of Romance" today!

572
00:37:04,590 --> 00:37:07,339
What? A moment of what?

573
00:37:07,339 --> 00:37:09,574
That Hong Kong movie...

574
00:37:10,692 --> 00:37:12,707
Never mind.

575
00:37:24,756 --> 00:37:26,381
Whoa, whoa!

576
00:37:26,381 --> 00:37:30,056
Did you see that? I almost just died!

577
00:37:30,056 --> 00:37:32,381
If I'd looked back, we'd both be dead.

578
00:37:32,381 --> 00:37:35,475
- Hold on tight.
- Okay!

579
00:37:53,333 --> 00:37:55,548
I finally feel alive again.

580
00:37:55,548 --> 00:37:57,714
Thanks, Yu Geon.

581
00:37:59,089 --> 00:38:00,423
Chae Yeon!

582
00:38:00,423 --> 00:38:01,660
Ha Na.

583
00:38:01,660 --> 00:38:03,094
Where have you been?

584
00:38:03,094 --> 00:38:04,840
I've been looking everywhere for you!

585
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:07,215
<i>She actually remembered my name.</i>

586
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:10,424
Look at the state of you!

587
00:38:10,424 --> 00:38:11,504
What is that on your head?

588
00:38:11,504 --> 00:38:12,799
A helmet.

589
00:38:12,799 --> 00:38:13,964
Wait.

590
00:38:13,964 --> 00:38:15,644
The helmet...

591
00:38:29,631 --> 00:38:30,823
Ma'am.

592
00:38:30,823 --> 00:38:32,443
Ma'am!

593
00:38:32,443 --> 00:38:34,945
Producer Jaden just landed.

594
00:38:34,945 --> 00:38:38,464
- What?
- Producer Jaden just landed.

595
00:38:38,464 --> 00:38:42,302
Should I book that sushi place
in Cheongdam for the meeting?

596
00:38:42,302 --> 00:38:44,964
- Why there?
- You said it was the best sushi of your life.

597
00:38:44,964 --> 00:38:49,895
Why would I take a Korean-American
to my all-time favorite sushi place?

598
00:38:49,895 --> 00:38:51,462
Word is he likes Korean food.

599
00:38:51,462 --> 00:38:53,402
Book a traditional Korean restaurant.

600
00:38:53,402 --> 00:38:55,903
- One that has really nice side dishes.
- Yes.

601
00:38:55,903 --> 00:38:58,322
- And about the meeting with Writer Noh...
- Hey!

602
00:38:58,322 --> 00:39:00,768
Ugh, just text it to me.

603
00:39:01,384 --> 00:39:03,975
Who on earth named this thing
the "Stairway to Heaven?"

604
00:39:03,975 --> 00:39:06,733
I'm staring straight at the gates of hell.

605
00:39:08,452 --> 00:39:11,897
Anyway, where did Ha Na run off to
in the middle of all this?

606
00:39:11,897 --> 00:39:13,964
Well...

607
00:39:13,964 --> 00:39:16,462
she was looking for someone.

608
00:39:19,089 --> 00:39:21,504
- And?
- So I found him for her.

609
00:39:21,504 --> 00:39:24,339
Just tell me who it is!

610
00:39:24,339 --> 00:39:26,127
Well...

611
00:39:28,831 --> 00:39:31,476
Are we playing "Twenty Questions" right now?

612
00:39:56,582 --> 00:39:58,826
Who are you?

613
00:40:06,506 --> 00:40:08,460
I came to return this.

614
00:40:10,840 --> 00:40:13,299
Something smells really good.

615
00:40:14,464 --> 00:40:17,428
I just got off my shift at a BBQ joint.

616
00:40:18,381 --> 00:40:20,756
By the way,

617
00:40:20,756 --> 00:40:23,434
the sunset from up here is gorgeous.

618
00:40:26,536 --> 00:40:28,617
How long have you been waiting here?

619
00:40:28,617 --> 00:40:30,756
You literally see me up there every single day.

620
00:40:30,756 --> 00:40:32,944
How are you not a fan?

621
00:40:42,798 --> 00:40:46,833
How did you even find my place?

622
00:40:50,840 --> 00:40:52,397
From this.

623
00:40:57,002 --> 00:40:58,849
[Sim Yu Geon]

624
00:41:00,133 --> 00:41:02,132
But my address isn't even on this.

625
00:41:02,132 --> 00:41:03,717
I can't stop thinking about it.

626
00:41:03,717 --> 00:41:05,665
Sorry? Thinking about what?

627
00:41:05,665 --> 00:41:08,396
Riding on your bike.

628
00:41:09,473 --> 00:41:12,567
I've never felt anything like that before.

629
00:41:16,464 --> 00:41:19,574
Could you take me for another spin sometime?

630
00:41:20,631 --> 00:41:22,203
Sure.

631
00:41:22,864 --> 00:41:24,673
But...

632
00:41:24,673 --> 00:41:27,104
why are you doing this?

633
00:41:27,104 --> 00:41:28,408
What's wrong with that?

634
00:41:28,408 --> 00:41:31,121
It's just...

635
00:41:31,121 --> 00:41:33,014
you're kind of scaring me.

636
00:41:34,339 --> 00:41:35,553
I'm scaring you?

637
00:41:35,553 --> 00:41:36,574
Well, it's just...

638
00:41:36,574 --> 00:41:39,579
This kind of stuff always works on TV.

639
00:41:39,579 --> 00:41:40,954
Works? What do you mean?

640
00:41:40,954 --> 00:41:43,233
I guess that only works on TV.

641
00:41:43,233 --> 00:41:46,423
Look, as you probably know,
I'm actually amazing at everything else.

642
00:41:46,423 --> 00:41:49,174
I can do forward rolls,
shoot a gun, ride horses,

643
00:41:49,174 --> 00:41:51,807
and even jump off high buildings.

644
00:41:51,807 --> 00:41:53,883
- Right.
- But...

645
00:41:55,173 --> 00:41:58,071
I have absolutely no idea how to make friends.

646
00:41:58,673 --> 00:42:01,282
Which is why I don't have any.

647
00:42:08,326 --> 00:42:10,088
Are you saying

648
00:42:10,708 --> 00:42:13,336
you want to be friends with me?

649
00:42:16,756 --> 00:42:18,433
I guess...

650
00:42:23,298 --> 00:42:24,840
Yeah.

651
00:42:24,840 --> 00:42:28,110
Then let's be...

652
00:42:28,110 --> 00:42:29,749
friends.

653
00:42:32,015 --> 00:42:33,673
You mean it?

654
00:42:33,673 --> 00:42:35,258
Yeah.

655
00:42:38,327 --> 00:42:42,281
Then consider this
a gift to celebrate our new friendship.

656
00:42:43,923 --> 00:42:45,047
Huh?

657
00:42:45,047 --> 00:42:46,923
I...

658
00:42:46,923 --> 00:42:49,534
I have to go now, friend.

659
00:42:49,534 --> 00:42:50,756
Bye.

660
00:42:50,756 --> 00:42:53,566
Bye, friend.

661
00:42:56,631 --> 00:43:00,341
Seems like she knows
exactly how to make friends.

662
00:43:22,306 --> 00:43:23,647
It's been a while, Jaden.

663
00:43:23,647 --> 00:43:25,127
Hello, CEO An.

664
00:43:25,127 --> 00:43:30,072
Or should I be calling you CEO Seo now?

665
00:43:30,072 --> 00:43:31,446
Whatever you're comfortable with.

666
00:43:31,446 --> 00:43:34,207
I never thought I'd see the day
you'd be smiling in front of me.

667
00:43:34,207 --> 00:43:38,038
Did that day come sooner than you expected?

668
00:43:38,038 --> 00:43:40,792
You've grown a thick skin.

669
00:43:40,792 --> 00:43:44,377
It's nice to see
you've lost some of that innocence.

670
00:43:44,377 --> 00:43:46,806
Let's order first.

671
00:43:46,806 --> 00:43:50,766
Talking business on an empty stomach
makes me nauseous.

672
00:44:00,477 --> 00:44:02,320
Here, let me.

673
00:44:04,882 --> 00:44:09,966
So, you're saying you're open to co-producing?

674
00:44:09,966 --> 00:44:11,905
Since I'm starting out in unfamiliar territory,

675
00:44:11,905 --> 00:44:14,449
I wanted someone I could trust to guide me.

676
00:44:14,449 --> 00:44:17,827
And you think I'm the right person for that?

677
00:44:17,827 --> 00:44:20,831
You're the one who reached out to me first.

678
00:44:20,831 --> 00:44:22,626
How naive.

679
00:44:22,626 --> 00:44:25,420
You have no idea what I might demand.

680
00:44:25,420 --> 00:44:29,491
Let's save the project talk
for when the first draft is ready.

681
00:44:31,135 --> 00:44:35,346
I'm actually much more interested
in the off-screen drama.

682
00:44:35,346 --> 00:44:37,087
How much are you willing to share with me?

683
00:44:37,087 --> 00:44:41,025
I'd be happy to share everything I know.

684
00:44:41,726 --> 00:44:43,807
I heard there's quite a backstory
to that script.

685
00:44:43,807 --> 00:44:47,466
Rumors say it involves a first love?

686
00:44:47,466 --> 00:44:51,653
That only applies
if we're official partners, though.

687
00:44:51,653 --> 00:44:53,699
Since we're not there yet,

688
00:44:53,699 --> 00:44:57,333
I need to be a bit careful.

689
00:45:10,019 --> 00:45:13,259
I'll reach out as soon
as the first draft is ready.

690
00:45:13,259 --> 00:45:14,792
Sounds good.

691
00:45:35,089 --> 00:45:37,474
- Hey.
- Yes?

692
00:45:37,474 --> 00:45:40,874
Why'd he come all this way
if he wasn't coming in?

693
00:45:40,874 --> 00:45:43,254
Maybe he's just uncomfortable?

694
00:45:45,256 --> 00:45:47,874
Uncomfortable? About what?

695
00:45:47,874 --> 00:45:49,927
I'm sorry.

696
00:45:55,506 --> 00:45:57,472
You don't have to walk on eggshells around me.

697
00:45:57,472 --> 00:45:59,474
You said CEO An is our best bet anyway.

698
00:45:59,474 --> 00:46:02,173
Yeah, for now, she is.

699
00:46:02,173 --> 00:46:06,235
And I'm not walking on eggshells.
I'm actually really pissed off right now.

700
00:46:07,964 --> 00:46:10,631
You need to get that script back from Yi Jae.

701
00:46:10,631 --> 00:46:12,290
- Why?
- What do you mean, why?

702
00:46:12,290 --> 00:46:16,569
You went on TV and blabbed all about a script
without even having a first draft.

703
00:46:16,569 --> 00:46:18,650
Every single person I meet brings it up.

704
00:46:18,650 --> 00:46:21,751
CEO An even brought up the first love rumor.

705
00:46:22,409 --> 00:46:24,496
Don't tell me...

706
00:46:24,496 --> 00:46:25,705
In Uk.

707
00:46:25,705 --> 00:46:27,610
Yes, I said it was me.

708
00:46:27,610 --> 00:46:30,301
I told her I was your first love.

709
00:46:34,256 --> 00:46:35,260
[Yi Jae]

710
00:46:38,840 --> 00:46:40,799
Yeah, hello?

711
00:46:40,799 --> 00:46:43,014
<i>Where are you? Get to Sangam right now.</i>

712
00:46:43,014 --> 00:46:44,519
<i>Producer Kyung wants a meeting.</i>

713
00:46:44,519 --> 00:46:46,734
<i>I'll text you the address.</i>

714
00:46:48,214 --> 00:46:49,720
Why are you going to a meeting?

715
00:46:49,720 --> 00:46:52,860
I have no idea why
you're even going to a meeting. Whatever.

716
00:46:52,860 --> 00:46:54,579
Just go

717
00:46:54,579 --> 00:46:56,906
and make sure that script is still alive.

718
00:46:56,906 --> 00:46:59,506
- Yes, boss.
- Right.

719
00:46:59,506 --> 00:47:01,305
Please get out.

720
00:47:17,051 --> 00:47:19,308
My phone!

721
00:47:34,548 --> 00:47:36,006
It's still early, let's get another round.

722
00:47:36,006 --> 00:47:37,964
That's enough. Your taxi's here.

723
00:47:37,964 --> 00:47:39,548
- Here!
- Who called it?

724
00:47:39,548 --> 00:47:41,256
- I did.
- You shouldn't have!

725
00:47:41,256 --> 00:47:42,506
Let's get one more round.

726
00:47:42,506 --> 00:47:44,787
Back to your wife you go.

727
00:47:44,787 --> 00:47:46,089
I don't want to go home

728
00:47:46,089 --> 00:47:48,538
- because of my wife.
- But you love her!

729
00:47:48,538 --> 00:47:50,749
Hey! I do not!

730
00:47:50,749 --> 00:47:53,548
- Make sure he gets home safe.
- Sure.

731
00:47:53,548 --> 00:47:55,840
- Alright.
- Seriously...

732
00:47:55,840 --> 00:47:59,306
I'm not going home!

733
00:48:02,262 --> 00:48:03,303
Wait, what?

734
00:48:03,303 --> 00:48:05,715
I thought we were having a meeting.

735
00:48:05,715 --> 00:48:07,183
- Huh?
- Is everyone gone?

736
00:48:07,183 --> 00:48:09,222
It's over.

737
00:48:09,222 --> 00:48:11,269
Why are you so late?

738
00:48:11,269 --> 00:48:14,025
You call this late?
I even printed out the prep sheets.

739
00:48:14,025 --> 00:48:15,123
And I called him, too.

740
00:48:15,123 --> 00:48:18,109
"Him?" Why did you bring a dog? Where is he?

741
00:48:18,109 --> 00:48:20,673
Woo Soo Bin. Director Ian Woo.

742
00:48:20,673 --> 00:48:23,214
Oh, him.

743
00:48:23,214 --> 00:48:26,451
Hey, he already agreed to do the show,

744
00:48:26,451 --> 00:48:27,994
so we're good.

745
00:48:27,994 --> 00:48:32,464
I'll take it from here, so you stay out of it.

746
00:48:32,464 --> 00:48:34,530
Since when do you handle things yourself?

747
00:48:34,530 --> 00:48:37,169
Did you even have a meeting today?

748
00:48:37,169 --> 00:48:40,090
Wait, did you just call me
to be your designated driver?

749
00:48:40,090 --> 00:48:42,224
Designated driver?

750
00:48:43,131 --> 00:48:45,603
Ding, ding, ding.

751
00:48:46,256 --> 00:48:48,807
Your driving is more comfortable

752
00:48:48,807 --> 00:48:51,989
than my own mattress.

753
00:48:51,989 --> 00:48:54,594
I'm counting on you.

754
00:48:57,882 --> 00:49:00,150
- She can't drive.
- Excuse me?

755
00:49:00,150 --> 00:49:02,006
She's been drinking.

756
00:49:02,006 --> 00:49:03,740
Huh?

757
00:49:03,740 --> 00:49:06,802
You had drinks with me, remember?

758
00:49:09,411 --> 00:49:10,968
I'm so dizzy.

759
00:49:10,968 --> 00:49:12,409
How am I even here?

760
00:49:12,409 --> 00:49:14,148
Why am I here?

761
00:49:14,148 --> 00:49:16,007
How did I get here? So dizzy...

762
00:49:16,007 --> 00:49:18,795
You were completely fine a second ago.
What are you talking about?

763
00:49:18,795 --> 00:49:20,789
This is why day drinking is the worst.

764
00:49:20,789 --> 00:49:23,764
I guess I do smell alcohol.

765
00:49:29,882 --> 00:49:30,964
Is he always like this?

766
00:49:30,964 --> 00:49:32,172
What?

767
00:49:32,172 --> 00:49:33,184
No, well...

768
00:49:33,184 --> 00:49:35,756
he does make me work when he's drunk,
dumps his crap on me,

769
00:49:35,756 --> 00:49:37,633
- and uses me as his driver, but...
- What?

770
00:49:37,633 --> 00:49:39,882
Hey! Ju Yi Jae!

771
00:49:39,882 --> 00:49:41,933
Still, he's not a bad guy.

772
00:49:41,933 --> 00:49:43,381
We've been friends since college,

773
00:49:43,381 --> 00:49:45,280
- almost a decade?
- Right?

774
00:49:45,280 --> 00:49:47,534
No. He really is a bad guy.

775
00:49:47,534 --> 00:49:48,744
Excuse me,

776
00:49:48,744 --> 00:49:51,793
what do you think
you're doing right in front of me?

777
00:49:51,793 --> 00:49:53,913
Then what exactly are you doing to Yi Jae?

778
00:49:53,913 --> 00:49:55,506
What?

779
00:49:55,506 --> 00:49:58,002
What are you talking about?

780
00:49:58,628 --> 00:50:00,539
I already know everything.

781
00:50:00,539 --> 00:50:03,399
Should I say it,
or do you want to tell her yourself?

782
00:50:03,399 --> 00:50:06,979
<i>They're canceling "Here Comes Yi Jae"
in the upcoming revamp.</i>

783
00:50:06,979 --> 00:50:08,820
<i>Can't you just do a better job, man?</i>

784
00:50:08,820 --> 00:50:12,840
<i>People are saying the producer is
riding the reporter's coattails.</i>

785
00:50:12,840 --> 00:50:14,440
<i>Just keep the ratings up.</i>

786
00:50:14,440 --> 00:50:16,120
<i>Even better if we hit a record high.</i>

787
00:50:16,120 --> 00:50:21,024
<i>Do that, and I'll make sure
your job is safe no matter what.</i>

788
00:50:21,024 --> 00:50:24,068
<i>I'll do my best.</i>

789
00:50:24,068 --> 00:50:25,868
I was just...

790
00:50:29,089 --> 00:50:31,268
Forget it.

791
00:50:31,268 --> 00:50:33,173
I'll hear it straight from him.

792
00:50:33,173 --> 00:50:34,882
Get in.

793
00:50:34,882 --> 00:50:36,173
What?

794
00:50:36,173 --> 00:50:37,590
I said, get in.

795
00:50:37,590 --> 00:50:39,702
Okay.

796
00:50:52,256 --> 00:50:53,806
I thought you were drinking.

797
00:50:53,806 --> 00:50:55,338
I didn't drink.

798
00:50:55,338 --> 00:50:57,143
Give me a straight answer.

799
00:50:57,143 --> 00:50:59,798
This is my mom's car!
I'm still making payments...

800
00:50:59,798 --> 00:51:01,006
What? Am I getting fired?

801
00:51:01,006 --> 00:51:03,073
I think I'm going to throw up.

802
00:51:06,527 --> 00:51:08,145
Hey, this...

803
00:51:12,631 --> 00:51:15,502
And you totally used me.

804
00:51:16,161 --> 00:51:17,566
Hey.

805
00:51:18,214 --> 00:51:19,895
Hey!

806
00:51:19,895 --> 00:51:21,995
Look, I'm sorry.

807
00:51:21,995 --> 00:51:25,713
But I had to save my own skin...

808
00:51:25,713 --> 00:51:29,006
No, that's not what I meant...

809
00:51:29,006 --> 00:51:31,268
Hey, watch the road!

810
00:51:34,089 --> 00:51:36,732
Watch out!

811
00:51:54,298 --> 00:51:58,316
Since when did you write me off?

812
00:51:58,316 --> 00:52:02,166
I know I could get fired at any moment,

813
00:52:02,166 --> 00:52:03,501
but this is crossing the line.

814
00:52:03,501 --> 00:52:05,831
Hey, Yi Jae...

815
00:52:05,831 --> 00:52:07,046
just listen to me.

816
00:52:07,046 --> 00:52:10,381
Hey, where are you going?

817
00:52:10,381 --> 00:52:12,840
What?

818
00:52:12,840 --> 00:52:15,436
You and I are done as of today.

819
00:52:15,436 --> 00:52:16,513
- Get out.
- Huh?

820
00:52:16,513 --> 00:52:17,590
I said, get out!

821
00:52:17,590 --> 00:52:18,725
Hey, hold on a second.

822
00:52:18,725 --> 00:52:20,923
- Get the hell out!
- No!

823
00:52:20,923 --> 00:52:22,979
Get out!

824
00:52:22,979 --> 00:52:24,882
Oh, no...

825
00:52:24,882 --> 00:52:26,407
I didn't...

826
00:52:26,407 --> 00:52:27,820
- Come here.
- I'll sew it up for you.

827
00:52:27,820 --> 00:52:30,100
Come here. Get out!

828
00:52:30,100 --> 00:52:31,662
Get out!

829
00:52:34,047 --> 00:52:36,111
Hey.

830
00:52:36,111 --> 00:52:37,923
Hey.

831
00:52:37,923 --> 00:52:39,256
My keys...

832
00:52:39,256 --> 00:52:40,299
Hey, what are you doing?

833
00:52:40,299 --> 00:52:42,256
Hey!

834
00:52:44,375 --> 00:52:45,993
No!

835
00:52:46,673 --> 00:52:49,304
You crazy...

836
00:52:51,803 --> 00:52:54,094
Hey! My keys...

837
00:52:58,131 --> 00:53:00,006
Where are they?

838
00:53:00,006 --> 00:53:03,068
Hey! Ju Yi Jae!

839
00:53:50,756 --> 00:53:52,715
I feel like...

840
00:53:52,715 --> 00:53:55,992
I've been rushing through life,

841
00:53:55,992 --> 00:53:59,208
just putting out fires as they come.

842
00:54:00,089 --> 00:54:02,995
Who would've thought
a job I took just for the money

843
00:54:02,995 --> 00:54:08,334
would turn into weeks, months, and years?

844
00:54:08,334 --> 00:54:11,303
That alone is impressive.

845
00:54:12,673 --> 00:54:14,798
That's why so many places want to book you.

846
00:54:14,798 --> 00:54:16,506
But...

847
00:54:16,506 --> 00:54:19,144
I'm not irreplaceable.

848
00:54:20,272 --> 00:54:24,292
Who else is going to show up
on "Here Comes Yi Jae" if you don't?

849
00:54:24,292 --> 00:54:26,027
You're right.

850
00:54:27,214 --> 00:54:29,313
I gave it the wrong title.

851
00:54:29,313 --> 00:54:31,574
I said "Here Comes Yi Jae!"

852
00:54:31,574 --> 00:54:33,943
and now I'm just gone.

853
00:54:36,074 --> 00:54:40,562
I didn't love the job,
but it meant a lot to me.

854
00:54:42,121 --> 00:54:46,713
It put food on the table and paid off my debts.

855
00:55:00,256 --> 00:55:02,149
You jerk.

856
00:55:03,798 --> 00:55:05,882
Why do you keep following me around?

857
00:55:05,882 --> 00:55:08,193
You won't even let me cry in peace.

858
00:55:34,023 --> 00:55:36,013
Ju Yi Jae.

859
00:55:44,548 --> 00:55:47,899
Now I see why you said
being pathetic is the worst.

860
00:55:49,673 --> 00:55:52,404
Because it stays with you forever.

861
00:55:57,131 --> 00:55:59,244
You do look...

862
00:56:00,590 --> 00:56:03,241
a bit pathetic...

863
00:56:03,241 --> 00:56:04,843
right now.

864
00:56:09,342 --> 00:56:12,130
Not that I could ever forget you anyway.

865
00:56:25,807 --> 00:56:27,602
Woo Soo Bin.

866
00:56:29,214 --> 00:56:32,152
My biggest regret isn't you.

867
00:56:33,882 --> 00:56:35,652
It's me.

868
00:58:17,506 --> 00:58:19,283
Ian.

869
00:58:25,506 --> 00:58:26,882
Let's go get some breakfast.

870
00:58:26,882 --> 00:58:28,625
In Uk.

871
00:58:34,298 --> 00:58:35,896
It's freezing.

872
00:59:36,618 --> 00:59:37,997
<i>I look forward to working with you.</i>

873
00:59:37,997 --> 00:59:41,170
<i>Please stay at the hotel
just until the studio is set up.</i>

874
00:59:41,170 --> 00:59:42,797
<i>You need to write.</i>

875
00:59:42,797 --> 00:59:44,538
<i>You were laughing at me earlier, weren't you?</i>

876
00:59:44,538 --> 00:59:46,178
<i>Who do you think you are,
messing with my friend?</i>

877
00:59:46,178 --> 00:59:47,798
<i>Come on, friend. Let's go.</i>

878
00:59:47,798 --> 00:59:51,218
<i>When you're stuck in the same house
and spending all day together,</i>

879
00:59:51,218 --> 00:59:53,554
<i>you naturally catch feelings,</i>

880
00:59:53,554 --> 00:59:57,177
<i>and it turns into a hot, R-rated romance.</i>

881
00:59:57,177 --> 00:59:59,256
<i>What are you even hesitating for?</i>

882
00:59:59,256 --> 01:00:00,882
<i>Looks like...</i>

883
01:00:00,882 --> 01:00:03,071
<i>we're about to do it right now.</i>

